"This document details a laboratory experiment focused on the design and implementation of Booth's multiplier using Verilog. The experiment requires participants to have a foundational understanding of logic gates, multipliers, registers, and 2's complement arithmetic. The core task involves analyzing a pre-existing Booth multiplier Verilog code, which is structured into separate datapath and control path modules. Participants are expected to identify any bugs present in this code, provide explanations for these issues, and subsequently implement corrections to rectify them."